According to the pilot's statement, the aircraft ballooned on touchdown due to an excessive 
approach airspeed and the nose wheel came down hard on the second runway contact.  After a 
short stop at Grand Canyon, the pilot departed on a flight to Las Vegas, Nevada.  After arrival 
at Las Vegas, the pilot discovered the damage to the nose gear strut and firewall during a 
routine postflight inspection of the aircraft. 
the pilot's use of an excessive approach airspeed and an improper bounced landing recovery 
technique. 
